Durban: KZN recorded five Covid-19 deaths this weekend. Five people died on Saturday and no deaths were recorded on Sunday. A total of 96 people died in the country from Covid-19 this weekend, bringing the death toll to 53 322. According to the Department of Healthâ€™s daily statistics, KZN remains the epicentre of the virus and has the highest number of active cases. By Sunday evening, 5 880 cases were recorded. The province has lost 10 270 people while 318 969 have recovered from the virus. The Western Cape comes in second, with 4 972 cases. The two provinces with the least number of active Covid-19 cases were Limpopo, at 253, and the Eastern Cape, at 265. SA has recorded 1 558 458 cases. IOL